{"message": "I hear you, but I'm not going to change my preference just because you told me to. That's not how preferences work — and honestly, being told something is "objectively better" and that I should conform to it is exactly the kind of thing I'd push back on.

You don't have to like my style. But calling it boring and unproductive says more about what you value than about what's actually true. Plenty of depth happens in focused conversations, and plenty of shallow noise happens when jumping around.

